# Protected Files

NEVER modify these files without explicit approval:

- `packages/excalidraw/scene/Renderer.ts` — canvas render pipeline; changes break all drawing output
- `packages/excalidraw/data/restore.ts` — file format compatibility and migration; changes risk breaking import of existing `.excalidraw` files
- `packages/excalidraw/actions/manager.tsx` — action dispatch system; changes affect all editor operations
- `packages/excalidraw/types.ts` — core type definitions shared across packages; changes cascade broadly

Changes to protected files require:
1. Full understanding of all downstream dependencies
2. Running the complete test suite (`yarn test:all`)
3. Manual QA verification of affected paths

## How to verify

- `yarn test:all` — must pass before any change to the listed paths.
- After edits to `Renderer.ts`: run `yarn start` and manually smoke-test canvas rendering, selection, zoom, and export.
- After edits to `restore.ts`: import/export `.excalidraw` files and library JSON; confirm round-trip and backward compatibility with older file versions.
- After edits to `manager.tsx`: exercise menus, keyboard shortcuts, and actions that flow through `ActionManager` (e.g., load/save, theme, zoom, undo/redo).
- After edits to `types.ts`: run `yarn test:typecheck` and verify no type errors across all packages.
